  "type": "feat",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 20th level, you take on aspects of the nature and appearance of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/undead/ghoul\">ghouls</a>. You no longer feel the need to eat and are immune to hunger (though you are still able to consume flesh if you choose to). You gain&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Immunity-Ex-or-Su-\">immunity</a>&nbsp;to cold,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Nonlethal-Damage\">nonlethal damage</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-Paralysis\">paralysis</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/s/sleep\">sleep</a>. You also gain&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Damage-Reduction-Ex-or-Su-\">DR</a>&nbsp;5/â€”. Additionally, you gain the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Stench-Ex-\">stench</a>&nbsp;ability with a radius of 10 feet. Creatures that fail their&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Fortitude\">Fortitude</a>&nbsp;saving throws are&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Sickened\">sickened</a>&nbsp;for 1d6+4 minutes. Use half your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/sorcerer\">sorcerer</a>&nbsp;level instead of half your racial&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Hit-Dice-HD-\">Hit Dice</a>&nbsp;to determine the saving throw DC.</p>",
